Linear Search Algorithm:

Input: An array (arr) and a target value (x).
Output: Index of x in arr if x is present; otherwise, -1.
Process:
Start from the beginning of the array (index = 0).
Compare each element of the array with x.
If a match is found, return the index of the element.
If the entire array is searched and no match is found, return -1.Liner Search algorithm :


Pseudocode for Linear Search:

LinearSearch(arr, n, x):
    // arr: array to be searched
    // n: size of array arr
    // x: element to be searched
    
    for i from 0 to n-1 do:
        if arr[i] == x then:
            return i  // Element found at index i
        end if
    end for
    
    return -1  // Element not found
